article.headline: Dell'Orso, Sinani lead Campbell over UNC Wilmington 105-100 in 2OT
article.description: — Anthony Dell'Orso had 34 points and 11 rebounds, Jasin Sinani scored 27 and Campbell outlasted UNC Wilmington 105-100 in double overtime on Monday night.
article.linkText: Dell'Orso, Sinani lead Campbell over UNC Wilmington 105-100 in 2OT
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. -- — Anthony Dell'Orso had 34 points and 11 rebounds, Jasin Sinani scored 27 and Campbell outlasted UNC Wilmington 105-100 in double overtime on Monday night. Dell'Orso and Sinani erased deficits with 3-pointers in the second extra period, but two free throws by Trazarien White tied it at 99 with 2:17 left. Laurynas Vaistaras made the second of two free throws to give the Fighting Camels (13-16, 7-9 Coastal Athletic Conference) the lead and Dell'Orso and Sinani both sank a pair in the final 19 seconds to preserve the victory. Sinani hit 4 of 6 from 3-point range and added five assists for Campbell. Elijah Walsh scored 15. White finished with a career-high 38 points and nine rebounds for the Seahawks (20-8, 11-5). Shykeim Phillips added 18 points and four assists, while Maleeck Harden-Hayes scored 14. Dell'Orso scored 13 points in the first half as Campbell took a 43-36 lead into intermission. Harden-Hayes hit a 3-pointer with 18 seconds left to force the first overtime tied at 81. White sent it to a second overtime when he hit two free throws with 23 seconds to go to tie it at 91. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
